==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*duru-'', from Indo-European ''*dhwer-, *dhur-''.  Cognate with Old Frisian [[dure]], Old Saxon ''duru''.  The Germanic word also existed with other stems: ''*dora-'' (see Old English [[dor]]), ''*duri-'' (see German [[Tür]]).  Indo-European cognates include Greek [[θυρα]], Latin [[foris]], Lithuanian [[durys|dùrys]], Old Church Slavonic [[двьрь]] (Russian [[дверь]]).

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/'dʊrʊ/}}

